Commentary: on the helmet grille! And the free hit goes for none. Short ball, a bit of extra pace. Nice rise, and that clatters Imam on the face. The physio is having a look

Commentary: good length ball, just outside leg stump. Imam tries to pull but misses. They collect the wide
Commentary_short: Steyn to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 wide

Commentary: length ball on middle. But he comes down the ground to convert it into a fuller ball, and then hammers it over deep midwicket for a maximum
Commentary_short: Steyn to Imam-ul-Haq, SIX runs

Commentary: wayward from Steyn now. Back of a length, quite far away from leg stump
Commentary_short: Steyn to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 wide

Commentary: good length, on middle. Runs it down to third man for a single
Commentary_short: Steyn to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: good length, just outside off stump. Fended off the back foot, back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Steyn to Kohler-Cadmore, no run

Commentary: the long over ends with a wicket! All those extra deliveries pay off for Steyn. Length ball, wide outside off. Kohler-Cadmore reaches out, tries to cut, and ends up slicing it instead. In the air, and Delport runs behind from point to take a sliding catch
Commentary_short: Steyn to Kohler-Cadmore, OUT
Dismissal_text: T Kohler-Cadmore c Delport b Steyn 4 (11m 4b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: sweet as! Fullish, just outside off. Sticks his bat out, and creams a boundary behind point for four.
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Haider Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length, outside off. Cut to short third man, and they're scampering across for one.
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: in the air, but just beyond the third-man fielder! Length ball rising above and he ramps this late! Nearly goes for a six, one bounce for four

Commentary: punished by this length ball angling down the leg side. Helps it along it's way to fine leg with a gentle guided flick
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Imam-ul-Haq, FOUR runs

Commentary: full, just outside off stump. Caresses a drive, and the ball goes through the hands of cover! Fielder then runs behind to stop the ball from going for four. Sarfaraz isn't angry though
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Imam-ul-Haq, 2 runs

Commentary: good length, on off stump. Flicked to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: good length ball, just outside leg stump. Through to Sarfaraz
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 wide

Commentary: nudges this full ball off his pads to square leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: gives it the treatment it deserves! Full toss, just outside off, and he absolutely hammers a six over the bowler's head! Allows him to free his arms, and he maximises on this freebie. Team fifty
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Haider Ali, SIX runs

Commentary: full outside off, and he creams a square drive! But diving stop by point saves a certain boundary
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: deft! And just past the diving short fine leg fielder, Shinwari. This is slighty slower from Hasnain, but Imam turns in with very soft hands off his hips
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Imam-ul-Haq, FOUR runs

Commentary: fullish, just outside off. Mistimes the cover drive to cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Imam-ul-Haq, no run

Commentary: back of a length, just outside leg stump, and flying over the head to Sarfaraz. Wide given for the line perhaps, but definitely for the height
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 wide

Commentary: full on middle, and flicked off his boots to the sweeper fielder on the leg side. Powerplay done
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle. He shuffles across, exposing leg stump, before nudging it to square leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: length ball, angling into him. Guided to square leg with gentle hands
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: good length, on off. Plays the late cut, but stopped by Hasnain at short third man diving to his right
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: full, on middle. Smothers it off the front foot to wide long on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: good length outside leg stump as Imam skips down the ground. Has to change his shot choice at the last moment. Uncomfortably flicks to square leg. Cat-and-mouse stuff
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: short and wide. Cut to point, but Gladiators won't mind. This was there to be put away
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: hit to long on for a single
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off. He comes down the ground and swats a cut to deep point
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: good length, on off . Pulled along the ground, in front of square, to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: good length, just outside off. Cut in the gap at deep point. They want two, but eventually settle for one
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: leading edge and chance of a run out! Tries to nudge it to the leg side but the ball goes towards the non-striker instead. Batsman is taking the single but the non-striker is slow to get off the blocks. Good throw to the keeper and he whips the bails off. But he's safe!
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: full on off. Whipped to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: width on offer and he's cut hard through backward point! Beats the dive of the man on the ring, Nawaz purses his lips
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Haider Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: looped up, drifting leg side as Haider skips out and punches to long-on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: round the wicket, skidding on to hit the pads and run behind square... was he playing a shot? The umpires deem it so
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 leg bye

Commentary: tossed up and he hacks across the line, just one to deep square leg off the inside half of the bat
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: spears this out towards the off-side tramlines as Imam jumps about in his crease, cuts for one, raises the fifty stand between these two
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nawaz to Imam-ul-Haq, 1 run

Commentary: dropped! Cut in the air towards backward point, but Hasnain shells it going to his left! Straightforward chance from a mishit by Haider, but it goes begging

Commentary: flighted, wide of off and he hops across to cut in front of square, well fielded to keep them to one
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: bowled him with a skidder! Imam stepped out and Zahid dragged it down in response, straightening on leg stump and slides under a cross-batted swipe to rattle the timbers! Takes the fielders out of the equation, and breaks the Zalmi stand

Commentary: looped up on leg side, Malik is batting in a headband, misses with a flick

Commentary: floated full on off and pushed into the covers
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: uses the feet, walks down and nudges to the right of the bowler, Zahid swoops and turns... misses with a throw at the non-striker's! Haider hurled himself for his ground, think he would have made it
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: pushes out a googly, slides down leg
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, 1 wide

Commentary: lobbed up, 91kph outside off and sliced through point to the boundary rider
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: length ball on off, the be-helmeted Malik taps it back watchfully
Commentary_short: Cutting to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: in the channel, fired down at 129kph and Malik cuts, gets a bottom edge into the turf through to Sarfaraz
Commentary_short: Cutting to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: slower ball, wide of the stumps and slapped to point, squirms away and out to deep cover for a second

Commentary: mullered back over the bowler's head! Full and straight, in the slot and Malik steadies himself to hit through the line, just a clip - but it goes a way back over the boundary boards

Commentary: back to bowling in the channel, maybe pace off and dabbed off the back foot to third man
Commentary_short: Cutting to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: drops short, smashed to deep square on the pull, well intercepted by Ayub and keeps them to one
Commentary_short: Cutting to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: taken at long-on... but Delport has to throw it back in as he travels over the rope! Couldn't get it near a team-mate, with Cutting coming around from deep midwicket. Saves a few runs, though
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: flighted legbreak, Malik skips out and plays behind his pad - appeal for lbw, but he was a long way down. Quetta review but I suspect it'll be ump's call because of the distance from the stumps. Yep, more than 3m, so even though it's shown to be hitting middle, Malik will survive
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: spears this flat down the leg side
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, 2 wides

Commentary: slashed off the back foot, Azam cuts it off with a full-length dive at backward point! Good stuff by the big fellow
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: skids through as Malik attempts to cut, was it pad first? Quetta again use their review, though looks to be well outside the line, even if it did flick the flap above the knee roll. Impact outside off, and I don't think it was hitting anyway. Malik actually bottom-edged his shot into his boot, the ball then deflecting off Sarfaraz's gloves... which would have been an unlucky way to get out!
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: tossed up, 88kph on off, driven down to long-off
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: short and wide and hammered through gully! Brings up the Zalmi 100, and a vital boundary to finish what was otherwise a good over. Saifi in deep conversation with his bowler. 'Animated', shall we say?

Commentary: shortish in the channel, drops back and cuts for a single
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length, 130kph, Haider throws the hands... bottom edges four past Sarfaraz! Not where he was aiming, but it skips away, despite short fine leg giving chase

Commentary: crunched through the covers! Sarfaraz is apoplectic with his bowler! Short and wide and Haider kitchen-sinks it for four... Quetta's captain is immediately up and in Shinwari's ear as he walks back to his mark

Commentary: smoked over deep midwicket! There's a fielder out there but he won't get across! Slower ball, cutter wide of off, but Haider moves into line and carts it hard and flat over the ropes

Commentary: back of a length, Haider bottom-edges a baseball slug back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: full and wide and larruped through the covers, Azam misfields coming in off the rope to give them a second

Commentary: steps out and swings for the hills, heaved all the way! Malik's dancing feet and flashing blade pick up six over long-on

Commentary: advances again and muscles four more straight! Not as clean a hit but he manufactures enough power to beat long-on coming across
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, FOUR runs

Commentary: looped up wide, plinks a drive for one
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: flat, 93kph outside off, cut off the back foot and finds the fielder
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: pushed through and beats the top edge as Haider cuts, Sarfaraz can't hold on to it either
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: steps out and pushes this for a single to finish another productive over - and that's 50 from 28 for Haider, finding some form in this chase
Commentary_short: Zahid Mahmood to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: pace off and he flubs to mid-off! Up towards the blockhole, loopy cutter from Steyn and Haider is through his shot, comes off the toe towards the edge of the ring, where Faf du Plessis bags it and tags it. The Steyn remover works for Quetta

Commentary: full and pushed to mid-off, straight to Nawaz, almost had time to run all the way to the stumps... but his underarm throw misses! Rutherford was gone for all money

Commentary: length, 139kph and tucked calmly through mid-on
Commentary_short: Steyn to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: shortish, maybe another cutter angling across, Rutherford drops it in front of point
Commentary_short: Steyn to Rutherford, 1 run

Commentary: fired in full on leg stump, Malik can only clip one off his pads to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Steyn to Shoaib Malik, 1 run

Commentary: length, 134kph on fourth stump, dabbed to third man - superb comeback over from Steyn, wicket and five runs conceded

Commentary: length ball, 114kph, Rutherford heaves at it, edged into his pads
Commentary_short: Cutting to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: full on leg stump, pace on and he's clipped down to long-on for one
Commentary_short: Cutting to Rutherford, 1 run

Commentary: fired in straight at the stumps, can only dig it out into the leg side
Commentary_short: Cutting to Shoaib Malik, 2 runs

Commentary: full toss from Cutting and it's helped over deep backward square! Swivels and scoops it up over the ropes - a much-needed boundary
Commentary_short: Cutting to Shoaib Malik, SIX runs

Commentary: pinned in front! Cutting skids one into Malik's pads and umpire Illingworth gives it straight away. Malik reviews, he has too, but the equation is against him, just needs to be clipping - and it is! Top of leg stump, after thumping the knee roll, and Malik is gone!

Commentary: length, slower delivery on fourth stump, Wahab guides it away through third man! Cheeky shot, lovely timing as he waited for it, picks up four

Commentary: over the wicket, back of a length at 134kph, miscued on the pull out towards deep midwicket

Commentary: full and very wide, would surely have been called if Wahab hadn't thrown the bat and scooped one through backward point
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Wahab Riaz, 1 run

Commentary: hard length in the channel, maybe a hint of swing as Rutherford slogs across the line and fails to connect
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: on a length, this time he collars it, smoked into the crowd at deep midwicket! Clean strike for six, and Saifi is ticking again!

Commentary: short length outside off but with pace off, Rutherford swings hard, but misses!
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: full on the stumps and flipped away through square leg, finishes the over with a single
Commentary_short: Usman Shinwari to Rutherford, 1 run

Commentary: round the wicket, hits the mark with a 144kph yorker, bunted through the covers for a single

Commentary: over the wicket, another full ball tailing on off and Wahab can only hack it for one via an inside edge

Commentary: wide full bunger this time, Rutherford maybe expecting a change-up and he slips and misses with a wild swing
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: pitched up but misses his yorker, Rutherford ships it straight back over long-off! Clubbed for six, Zalmi are still in this!

Commentary: another half-volley, creamed over long-off for six more! Hasnain misses his length again and pace on goes just as quickly off the bat! Rutherford swinging haymakers

Commentary: over the wicket, goes short and he can't connect with a pull! Crucial dot ball gets him out of the over
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: full outside off, swatted through the leg side
Commentary_short: Steyn to Wahab Riaz, 1 run

Commentary: short ball heaved over deep square leg! Rutherford continues to hit them clean as a whistle, swivels and lands it just beyond the ropes
Commentary_short: Steyn to Rutherford, SIX runs

Commentary: low full toss, 141kph and Rutherford swings hard, inside-edges one into the leg side
Commentary_short: Steyn to Rutherford, 1 run

Commentary: full and wide and cruuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuunched! Steyn throws his head back as Wahab mows him over long-on, 102 metres! Zalmi are roaring back to life here

Commentary: fired in and clipped leg side, they amble one

Commentary: uproots leg stump! The Gladiators hit back at the death, Wahab dispatched by a searing yorker! Hasnain punches the air, though it's a tad forlorn. Wahab's job is done

Commentary: thumped into the covers and Rutherford is running regardless... Mahmood run out at the non-striker's end! He started, he stopped, having picked out the man, and then wasn't even in the frame. But they have got Rutherford at the right end
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Mahmood, OUT
Dismissal_text: S Mahmood run out (Mohammad Nawaz/Mohammad Hasnain) 0 (2m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: wide full toss, flies away to the rope, and that's pretty much the game! Rutherford is celebrating already, the ball slipped out and went yards wide of Sarfaraz, five wides to Zalmi and the scores are level!

Commentary: pitched up and drilled through the covers, Zalmi win by three wickets!
Commentary_short: Mohammad Hasnain to Rutherford, FOUR runs
